parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Emission Control System Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power and potentially lead to accidents, especially when driving uphill. The emission control system malfunction can lead to decreased fuel efficiency and increased emissions.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls while driving
especially uphill
and may restart after a few minutes. The driver may receive notifications from the manufacturer about an emission control system malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stopping of the vehicle can cause accidents, especially if other vehicles are following closely behind.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly stops in the middle of the road
often without warning
and may be accompanied by a flashing red light on the instrument panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shattering of the sunroof can cause injury to occupants, especially if they are hit by flying glass or exposed to the elements.
symptoms: The sunroof suddenly shatters while driving
often without warning
and can cause damage to the vehicle and injury to occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the vehicle stalls or dies
the transmission makes unusual noises or vibrations
the transmission warning light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine knocking or pinging noise can be a sign of premature engine wear, potentially leading to engine damage or failure, which can cause a loss of power, decreased fuel efficiency, and increased emissions.
symptoms: Abnormal knocking or pinging sound from the engine
typically when driving from a complete stop
no warning lights illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Pedestrian Actuator System (Hood Airbag) Deployment and Repair Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deployment of the pedestrian actuator system can cause damage to the hood and surrounding components, leading to safety concerns and difficulties in repairing the vehicle. The lack of proper training and repair procedures can result in prolonged repair times, leaving the vehicle inoperable and the owner without a safe mode of transportation.
symptoms: Unintended deployment of the hood airbag
hood opens from the back and cannot be closed
broken hood hinges
warning lights indicating the hood is open
malfunctioning interior lights
altered headlight performance with reduced beam light.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A sudden and unexpected fire can occur in the infotainment system, potentially causing damage to the vehicle, nearby structures, and posing a risk to occupants and bystanders.
symptoms: Spontaneous ignition of the infotainment system
melting of electrical components
spread of fire to other parts of the vehicle
soot and debris deposition throughout the interior.
